description.narrative:
The Somalia Stability Fund II (SSF) is a multi-donor fund that supports the development of a peaceful, stable, and secure Somalia. The Fund is designed to support enhanced government legitimacy and reduced political and communal conflict by increasing government visibility and community engagement; enhancing popular participation in governance, particularly for women and marginalised groups; and addressing structural drivers of conflict and instability at the political and communal level. 
The Fund is centred around Three pillars; 
1. Stabilization- Strengthened social cohesion and community-government relations in target areas.2. State-building- a. Better functioning, more accountable and responsive government institutions; b. Increased participation and representation of women and excluded groups in governance structures.3. Conflict prevention- Communities' vulnerability to conflict has been reduced.
